					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12498093#post-4356213</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12498093/scp-4265#post-4356213</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 09 Sep 2019 00:08:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's a really cool concept, but the execution left something to be desired. The snake-friendly modifications to films was cool on the first log, but it gets overplayed. Like the use of &quot;Black Mamba&quot; is great because takes you a second to realize what's going on.</p> <p>I really want to see this article explore something in our ophidian film connoisseur. Surely they have more personality than just being a snake that like snakes.</p> <p>Overall, neutralvote.</p> <p>(Side note it's &quot;Foundation&quot;, not &quot;foundation&quot;)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
